; Real nucleic-acid sequences with known secondary structure, for examples and
; benchmarking. Unlike random sequences these have genuine hairpins, stems, and
; multi-branch junctions, so they exercise the folding search realistically.
;
; RNA: the canonical yeast tRNA-Phe plus structured RNAs from seqfold's
; regression set (SPOT-RNA benchmark inputs, each with a published UNAFold
; reference free energy). DNA: structured oligos from the regression set,
; including explicit three- and four-branch folds.
;
; Header fields: name  len=<nt>  ref_dg=<UNAFold/literature kcal/mol>
;                seqfold_dg=<this tool, 37C>  -- description

